design:
Port the macOS path canonicalization from Go beads to beads-rs.

## Problem

macOS (and Windows) have case-insensitive but case-preserving filesystems. This causes issues with:
1. **Daemon socket discovery**: `/Users/foo/Desktop` vs `/users/foo/desktop` treated as different workspaces
2. **Remote URL matching**: Git worktrees with different case don't match
3. **Path comparisons**: String comparison fails for semantically identical paths

## Go beads solution

Use `realpath(1)` on macOS to resolve paths to their true filesystem case:
```go
func resolveCanonicalCase(path string) string {
    if runtime.GOOS == "darwin" {
        cmd := exec.Command("realpath", path)
        output, err := cmd.Output()
        if err == nil {
            return strings.TrimSpace(string(output))
        }
    }
    return ""
}
```

This ensures `/Users/foo/Desktop` always resolves to the true case, regardless of how user typed it.

## Implementation approach

**Core path utilities** (`src/core/path.rs`):
```rust
use std::path::{Path, PathBuf};

/// Canonicalize path, resolving symlinks and true case on case-insensitive FS
pub fn canonicalize_path(path: &Path) -> Result<PathBuf> {
    // 1. Convert to absolute
    let abs = path.canonicalize()
        .or_else(|_| std::env::current_dir().map(|cwd| cwd.join(path)))?;

    // 2. Resolve symlinks
    let canonical = abs.canonicalize().unwrap_or(abs);

    // 3. On case-insensitive FS, resolve to true case
    #[cfg(any(target_os = "macos", target_os = "windows"))]
    {
        if let Ok(resolved) = resolve_true_case(&canonical) {
            return Ok(resolved);
        }
    }

    Ok(canonical)
}

#[cfg(target_os = "macos")]
fn resolve_true_case(path: &Path) -> Result<PathBuf> {
    use std::process::Command;

    let output = Command::new("realpath")
        .arg(path)
        .output()
        .map_err(|e| Error::PathCanonicalization(e.to_string()))?;

    if !output.status.success() {
        return Err(Error::PathCanonicalization(
            String::from_utf8_lossy(&output.stderr).to_string()
        ));
    }

    let resolved = String::from_utf8_lossy(&output.stdout)
        .trim()
        .to_string();

    Ok(PathBuf::from(resolved))
}

#[cfg(target_os = "windows")]
fn resolve_true_case(path: &Path) -> Result<PathBuf> {
    // On Windows, fs::canonicalize already handles case
    // Just return the input
    Ok(path.to_path_buf())
}

#[cfg(not(any(target_os = "macos", target_os = "windows")))]
fn resolve_true_case(path: &Path) -> Result<PathBuf> {
    Ok(path.to_path_buf())
}

/// Normalize path for comparison (lowercase on case-insensitive FS)
pub fn normalize_path_for_comparison(path: &Path) -> Result<PathBuf> {
    let canonical = canonicalize_path(path)?;

    #[cfg(any(target_os = "macos", target_os = "windows"))]
    {
        // Lowercase for comparison
        let lowered = canonical.to_str()
            .ok_or(Error::InvalidUtf8Path)?
            .to_lowercase();
        return Ok(PathBuf::from(lowered));
    }

    #[cfg(not(any(target_os = "macos", target_os = "windows")))]
    {
        Ok(canonical)
    }
}

/// Compare two paths for equality (handles case-insensitive FS)
pub fn paths_equal(a: &Path, b: &Path) -> Result<bool> {
    let a_norm = normalize_path_for_comparison(a)?;
    let b_norm = normalize_path_for_comparison(b)?;
    Ok(a_norm == b_norm)
}
```

**Usage in daemon**:
```rust
// Socket discovery
let workspace = canonicalize_path(&env::current_dir()?)?;
let socket_path = socket_path(&workspace);

// Remote URL matching
let canonical_workspace = canonicalize_path(workspace)?;
if paths_equal(&canonical_workspace, &stored_workspace)? {
    // Same workspace
}
```

**Error type**:
```rust
#[derive(Debug, thiserror::Error)]
pub enum Error {
    #[error("Path canonicalization failed: {0}")]
    PathCanonicalization(String),

    #[error("Path contains invalid UTF-8")]
    InvalidUtf8Path,
}
```

